               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391021-name-1258" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-1258" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-1258" type="surname" value="BERTRAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-1258" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH BERTRAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a widow, and live in Devonshire buildings, Dover-road. The prisoner was in my service as a work-woman—she went sway on a Saturday night in July, and promised to come again on the Monday, but she did not—a day or two after, I missed the binding and these other articles—these are the articles—I can swear to then—one of them has a mark on it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was I not obliged to leave you, being ill—you laid this binding was new, and it is only old? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> She was ill, but I do not think that was the cause of her leaving—she went away very well on the Saturday night—this binding was not new, but it belongs to a sat of curtains.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18391021-name-1259" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18391021-name-1259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
